To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Please provide the complete secret blacklist that was used in 2021, to identify Mr William Yurek as someone "known to be hostile to police and fire crews."
If this list was obtained from the FBI, NCIC, or some other source, then please also provide documents that identify the source of the blacklist.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Winter Calvert

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1.  Please provide documents which detail the number of FBI agents or employees assigned to work at Fusion Centers in the United States during 2022.
Fusion Centers are defined by the DHS here:  https://www.dhs.gov/fusion-center-locations-and-contact-information

2.  Please provide documents which detail the number of FBI agents or employees assigned to work at centers outside the United States during 2022.

3.  Please provide documents that list or show FBI offices in foreign countries, and the number of FBI employees that are stationed there, during 2022.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Winter Calvert

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

For the years, 2018, 2019, 2020, 2021, and 2022:
1.  Please provide documents that detail the number of names on the  Terrorist Screening Database (TSDB), worldwide.  
2.  Please also provide documents that break down these numbers into Handling Codes 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5.
2.  Please provide documents that detail the number of names on the TSDB for only the United States, showing the numbers in Handling Codes 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Winter Calvert

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1.  Please provide documents that detail the bonus structure for executives at the FBI, at Grade GS-15 and above, for the years 2021 and 2022.
2.  Please provide documents that detail the bonuses that were paid to FBI executives, at Grade GS-15 and above, related to terrorism cases,  for the years 2021 and 2022.
3.  Please provide documents that detail the compensation and bonuses of former FBI TSC Director, Charles Kable (who retired in January 2023),  for the years 2021 and 2022.
4.  Please provide documents that detail the compensation and bonuses of FBI Director, Christopher Wray, especially those bonuses related to terrorism cases,  for the years 2021 and 2022.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Winter Calvert
